                            <mrow>\amp=\sqrt{25+144}</mrow>
                            <mrow>\amp=\sqrt{169}</mrow>
                            <mrow>\amp=13</mrow>
                        </md>The diagonal length of a rectangle with length <quantity><mag>5</mag><unit prefix="centi" base="meter"/></quantity> and width <quantity><mag>12</mag><unit prefix="centi" base="meter"/></quantity> is <quantity><mag>13</mag><unit prefix="centi" base="meter"/></quantity>.
                    </p></li>

                    <li><p>When <m>L=4</m> and <m>W=10</m>, we have:<md>
                            <mrow>\sqrt{L^2+W^2} \amp= \sqrt{4^2+10^2}</mrow>
                            <mrow>\amp=\sqrt{16+100}</mrow>
                            <mrow>\amp=\sqrt{116}</mrow>
                            <mrow>\amp\approx 10.77</mrow>
                        </md>The diagonal length of a rectangle with length <quantity><mag>4</mag><unit base="foot"/></quantity> and width <quantity><mag>10</mag><unit base="foot"/></quantity> is about <quantity><mag>10.77</mag><unit base="foot"/></quantity>.
                    </p></li>
                </ol></p>
            </solution>
        </exercise>

